# seed-alert cron schedule
# Install with:   crontab -e     (then paste one of the lines below)
# Verify with:    crontab -l
# Logs go to:     seed-alert/seed-alert.log
#
# NOTE: cron's finest granularity is 1 minute. For sub-minute frequency,
#       use the in-process loop instead:  python3 seed.py --interval 15
#
# ┌───────────── minute (0-59)
# │ ┌───────────── hour (0-23)
# │ │ ┌───────────── day of month (1-31)
# │ │ │ ┌───────────── month (1-12)
# │ │ │ │ ┌───────────── day of week (0-6, Sun=0)
# │ │ │ │ │
# * * * * *  command

# Every minute:
* * * * * /home/developer/Desktop/DAY\ TO\ DAY/defect-management/seed-alert/run-seed.sh

# Every 5 minutes:
# */5 * * * * /home/developer/Desktop/DAY\ TO\ DAY/defect-management/seed-alert/run-seed.sh

# Every hour on the hour:
# 0 * * * * /home/developer/Desktop/DAY\ TO\ DAY/defect-management/seed-alert/run-seed.sh
